review_blob: Wathery aftertaste. Lacks body and carbornation. The Rosted aromas is weak. We Wanted more.
Great stiff foam. Many nuances and complex beer. A little too sweet for our taste, thus, the beer could take a bit more hops.
Fresh and hopper IPA with little bitterness. Clear, crisp and a beer one can drink many of.
Jepper thinks it has a Strange aftermatch and he is convinced he can do better. I love the burnt various aromas.
